  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1485",
  "title": "Map search phrase to different indexes",
  "body": "Hi,\n\ni am looking to create a search where the user searches \"fast car\" and the response is ordered by speed in descending order with all cars where max_speed (int) >=180? Another example is a user searches for \"cheap women shoes\" and get all women shoes with a price lower than 50 ordered by price ascending.\n\nWhat's the best way to implement this behaviour? My first idea was to create a master search index in front with a few documents for fast/slow, cheap/expensive, dark/light, etc. These results map to the real indexes with their own order. But there are some disadvantages like many indexes and more operations which result in higher cost.\n\nI am very excited to receive your ideas.\n",
